cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a new approach to address the intra-camera supervision problem, which involves both learning within each camera view and inter-camera identity association. This requires machine learning techniques, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves mining quintuplet loss, which is a metric learning technique, and graph-based ID association, which involves graph theory, suggesting that cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of inter-camera identity association, which involves security and privacy, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category.
